Seven suspects charged for allegedly killing two farm dwellers return to the Piet Retief Magistrate's court. The two men were allegedly tortured to death in August last year. They were accused of livestock theft. Some of the suspects are also charged with the murder of the Coka siblings. eNCA senior reporter, Siphamandla Goge shares more details. Courtesy #DStv403  PIET RETIEF - Seven suspects charged for allegedly killing Sifiso Thwala and Musa Nene return to the Piet Retief magistrate’s court. The two men were allegedly tortured to death in August last year. They were accused of livestock theft. The accused include three who are charged in another murder case siblings Zenzele and Mgcini Coka. They're facing murder, attempted murder, kidnapping and defeating the ends of justice charges.